structure.unit: SERVICE OF PROCESS ON NONRESIDENT MOTORISTS

law.text:
As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Motor vehicles" means all motor propelled vehicles, except electric and steam railways.
"Public highway" means every street, road or highway in this state.
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 12-6.
